# Rust Oxide/uMod Plugin Development Rules

## CRITICAL ‚Äî Automatic Deploy

After editing any .cs plugin file, you MUST run `rust_plugin_push` BEFORE finishing your response. Do NOT wait for the user to ask. Deploy is the final step of every plugin edit ‚Äî run it automatically, then report the result. NEVER finish a response without deploying if you edited a plugin.

## Tool Invocation Policy

Each MCP tool has a correct moment. Follow the phase model:

### Phase A: Research (before writing code) ‚Äî works WITHOUT RCON
- BEFORE writing plugin code, search for hooks with `rust_docs_search_hook`
- BEFORE using any hook, get its exact signature with `rust_docs_get_hook`
- NEVER guess hook signatures ‚Äî always verify against live documentation
- Skip if you already looked up the same hooks earlier in this session

### Phase B: Deploy ‚Äî Fix ‚Äî Redeploy Loop (MANDATORY)
- Call `rust_plugin_push` after ANY code change ‚Äî ALWAYS, before finishing your response
- rust_plugin_push waits 5s, checks oxide logs AND RCON console AND server console log (output.txt) for runtime errors
- If `errors`, `runtimeErrors`, or `consoleErrors` in result ‚Äî fix immediately and redeploy. Repeat until success
- `consoleErrors` include: prefab not found, Unity exceptions, plugin initialization failures
- Grant permissions via `rust_grant_permission` ONLY on first push with new permissions
- Read config via `rust_read_config` ONLY on first push with config or after config structure change
- Do NOT ask the user to manually copy, reload, or check anything

### Phase C: Post-deploy verification
- rust_plugin_push already checks oxide logs + RCON console + server console log (output.txt) after 5s ‚Äî no separate call needed
- Call `rust_check_runtime_errors` to re-verify if user reports issues
- Call `rust_read_console_log` to inspect raw server console output (prefab errors, Unity exceptions)
- Call `rust_plugin_performance` ONLY for heavy hooks or when user reports lag

### Phase D: Finalization (plugin is done)
- Call `rust_generate_tests` ONLY when plugin is feature-stable and user confirms it's ready
- Call `rust_generate_docs` ONLY when user says plugin is complete / ready for release
- Do NOT call these during active development ‚Äî output is immediately outdated

## Plugin Structure
- All plugins use `namespace Oxide.Plugins;`
- All plugins have `[Info("Name", "Author", "Version")]` ‚Äî name MUST match filename
- All plugins inherit from `RustPlugin` (preferred) or `CovalencePlugin`

## Cleanup in Unload()
- ALWAYS destroy repeating timers
- ALWAYS destroy CUI for all players
- ALWAYS save data if applicable

## Error Handling
- Check entity validity: `entity != null && !entity.IsDestroyed`
- Wrap config loading in try/catch
- Use `PrintError()` / `PrintWarning()` for diagnostics
